JOHANNESBURG - Brickz has announced that he will be releasing a new single and collaboration album. The Kwaito star was accused of rape in 2013 and the case is still pending. Brickz had previously said the case wrecked his life and heavily affected his income. But, he has since embarked on a path to get back on track. eNCA.com met up with Brickz to see how he is coping with furthering his career while the claim still lingers over his head. * Watch the interview by Nonkululeko Ngqola in the gallery above. eNCA